                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/317: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-05T15:00:00-05:45"
                            >July 5, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>180. Your telegram 94, July 1, 5 p.m. President Moncada expressed his thanks for
                    your message and requested me to convey to you the assurance that he accepts the
                    award of the King of Spain and hopes to be prepared to appoint a commission to
                    locate the boundary as soon as public order has been restored along the
                    frontier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
